Kalpataru to Build Power Grid in Ukraine for 129.6 Million Euros

-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 
2011-04-22T12:45:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-22/kalpataru-to-build-power-grid-in-ukraine-for-129-6-million-euros.html
Kalpataru Power Transmission Ltd. (KPP) ,
India’s manufacturer of transmission towers, will build a power
line from Ukraine’s Rivnenska nuclear power station to the
country’s capital Kiev to increase supplies.  Ukraine’s state company NEK Ukrenergo and Kalpataru signed
the contract worth of 129.6 million euros ($188.6 million)
today, the Energy and Coal Industry Ministry of the former
Soviet state said in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daryna Krasnolutska in Kiev at 
 dkrasnolutsk@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
